MPARISON:#{2}":[137,140],"##Enhanced Technical [[vpc-flow-logs|Notes]] for ADR - Transit Gateway vs. VPC Peering vs. PrivateLink#CONTEXTUALIZATION WITHIN THE AWS ECOYSTEM:":[141,146],"##Enhanced Technical [[vpc-flow-logs|Notes]] for ADR - Transit Gateway vs. VPC Peering vs. PrivateLink#CONTEXTUALIZATION WITHIN THE AWS ECOYSTEM:#**[[Transit gateway]]**: Integrates with [[cloudformation]] for automation, [[00_Master_Links_and_Intro|IAM]] for [[appsync|security]], and [[route53]] for DNS management. Fits well into hybrid architectures and multi-account setups.":[143,143],"##Enhanced Technical [[vpc-flow-logs|Notes]] for ADR - Transit Gateway vs. VPC Peering vs. PrivateLink#CONTEXTUALIZATION WITHIN THE AWS ECOYSTEM:#**[[AWS_SA_PRO_Obsidian_Notes/Master/VPC|VPC]] Peering**: Works seamlessly with [[route53]] for internal DNS resolution and integrates with [[00_Master_Links_and_Intro|IAM]] and [[appsync|Security]] Groups.":[144,144],"##Enhanced Technical [[vpc-flow-logs|Notes]] for ADR - Transit Gateway vs. VPC Peering vs. PrivateLink#CONTEXTUALIZATION WITHIN THE AWS ECOYSTEM:#**[[AWS_SA_PRO_Obsidian_Notes/Master/Networking/PrivateLink|PrivateLink]]**: Complements services like [[AWS_SA_PRO_Obsidian_Notes/Master/S3|S3]], [[00_Master_Links_and_Intro|RDS]], etc., by providing secure access through [[AWS_SA_PRO_Obsidian_Notes/Master/03-networking/privatelink|VPC endpoints]].":[145,146],"##Enhanced Technical [[vpc-flow-logs|Notes]] for ADR - Transit Gateway vs. VPC Peering vs. PrivateLink#REAL-WORLD USE CASES:":[147,152],"##Enhanced Technical [[vpc-flow-logs|Notes]] for ADR - Transit Gateway vs. VPC Peering vs. PrivateLink#REAL-WORLD USE CASES:#{1}":[149,149],"##Enhanced Technical [[vpc-flow-logs|Notes]] for ADR - Transit Gateway vs. VPC Peering vs. PrivateLink#REAL-WORLD USE CASES:#{2}":[150,150],"##Enhanced Technical [[vpc-flow-logs|Notes]] for ADR - Transit Gateway vs. VPC Peering vs. PrivateLink#REAL-WORLD USE CASES:#{3}":[151,152],"##Enhanced Technical [[vpc-flow-logs|Not